class="Greek"><span id="iii.vii.xix-p22.7"></span>ἐστὶ περὶ
᾽Αβρα€μ</span>: *De Abrahamo.* It opens the second division of the third
great group of writings on the Pentateuch (see note 11, above): the
biographical division, mentioning Enos, Enoch and Noah, Abraham, Isaac
